 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W3-003: Intern Attribute strings to eliminate repeated heap allocation. PROBLEM: Attribute wraps String. Every datom insertion clones the Attribute into entity_index, attribute_index, AVET index, and live_view (131 .clone() calls in store.rs). With ~200 unique attributes across 123K datoms, this creates ~500K redundant String allocations. First principle: a bounded, known set of values should be interned, not heap-allocated per instance. SOLUTION: (1) Create an AttributeInterner that maps String → AttributeId (u32 or u16 index). (2) Attribute becomes Copy (just a u16/u32). (3) The interner lives in Store and is populated from schema. (4) Index keys use AttributeId instead of Attribute, eliminating clone cost. (5) intern() at schema registration; lookup() at transact time. VERIFICATION: (1) Attribute is Copy (compile check). (2) Memory benchmark: store with 123K datoms uses < 60MB (was ~100-250MB). (3) Performance benchmark: transact throughput improved. (4) All existing tests pass. DEPENDS-ON: None (can be done independently). INTERACTS-WITH: W3-004 (index-by-offset — complementary optimization), W3-005 (live_projections — both reduce allocation)."
